# Cursor ignore patterns for an llm-wiki project.
#
# Stamped to `.cursorignore` at the project root by scripts/instantiate.sh
# when --agent=cursor or --agent=all (then this .template file is removed).
# Consumed once at instantiation time; not refreshed by
# scripts/update-from-template.sh. Edit `.cursorignore` in your project
# freely after it is generated.
#
# What .cursorignore controls: paths excluded from Cursor's indexing, @-file
# context, and agent file search. It does NOT affect git tracking (that is
# .gitignore). See wiki/agents/cursor/README.md "Controlling what Cursor
# sees" for the full mechanism table.

# Claude Code overlay artifacts. A Cursor target project has native
# .cursor/ rules and skills, so the parallel Claude instructions are
# duplicate context Cursor should not index or surface.
CLAUDE.md
.claude/
.claude/**
wiki/agents/claude-code/

# NOTE: the shared, agent-agnostic wiki discipline files are deliberately
# NOT ignored — Cursor skills and the postToolUse hook reference them:
#   wiki/agents/discipline-gates.md
#   wiki/agents/verification-gate.md
#   wiki/agents/wiki-write-protocol.md
#   wiki/agents/templates/ensure-wiki.py
